description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Primary Care Network (PCN) Lead&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Are you a great communicator with excellent interpersonal skills?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Do you have excellent organisational skills?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Could you build relationships with GPs, Practice Managers, people who use services in primary care, the voluntary sector, health and social care teams to help the Primary Care Network to deliver their contracted services effectively and in a way that helps to make the most of local assets? &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Are you passionate about working within primary care to help people to live healthily within communities? &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;If you answered yes to our questions, we’ve got the perfect role for you! &lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; You will need to be an excellent listener, deeply curious about people, and what keeps us well, happy to roll up your sleeves to ‘make things happen’ and be prepared to work in a new role that will grow and develop as you do. The ability to work on your own initiative is essential, though you must also be a good team player. &lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;What we offer&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Our aim&lt;/strong&gt; – &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Empowering people to self-manage health and social needs and improve the quality of life&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We encourage staff to get involved in exploring new ways of working and service development, with opportunities for CPD along the way. You’ll be able to develop your skills in a friendly and supportive team.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;So what are you waiting for? We can’t wait to hear from you, and look forward to receiving your application. &lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; We believe that anyone who is really interested in the role will want to organise an informal chat – so please contact Peta Stross (Chief Operating Officer) or Sue Turner (Neighbourhood Lead). To make arrangements for an informal chat please contact the team via Jane Ashworth, &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;jane.ashworth@nhs.net&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt; 0161 983 0565.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;SPCT is a Community Interest Company&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NHS Pension scheme provider&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;12 months fixed term contract or secondment&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interviews to be scheduled for week commencing 23rd November&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;*Due to COVID-19 interviews will be held virtually*&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
